Title: NP-Completeness of Minimum Rule Sets  
Author: Tim L. Andersen and Tony R. Martinez 
Keyword: Key Words: Rule Induction, Machine Learning, NP-Completeness.  
Address: Provo, Utah 84602  
Affiliation: Computer Science Department, Brigham Young University,  
Note: Proceedings of the 10th International Symposium on Computer and Information Sciences, pp. 411-418, 1995.  
Abstract: Rule induction systems seek to generate rule sets which are optimal in the complexity of the rule set. This paper develops a formal proof of the NP-Completeness of the problem of generating the simplest rule set (MIN RS) which accurately predicts examples in the training set for a particular type of generalization algorithm algorithm and complexity measure. The proof is then informally extended to cover a broader spectrum of complexity measures and learning algorithms. 
