Reference-contexts: This paper presents a formal proof concerning the NP-Completeness of the problem of generating minimum complexity (simple) rule sets. The proof uses a straightforward transformation from minimum set cover to show that this problem is NP-Complete. This transformation is similar to that used by <ref> (Van Horn 1994) </ref> for the minimum feature set problem. Due to the nature of this transformation, it can also be shown that the minimum rule set problem is at least as hard to approximate as minimum set cover.
